records.addlTxt:
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 09-08-15 at 5:00 p.m.;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence which includes successful completion of probation, no dirty UAs and no possession of any drugs.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
Minutes.
